  <bioghist id="aspace_e3a079ddd10ef1536305b528ec405f10">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Dr. Raymond J. Garbutt was the chief veterinarian of the American Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals in New York City in the 1920s.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_4c8d4bdbf2af5150f28c9a401992decd">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Writings, scrapbooks, photographs and lantern slides from Dr. Raymond J. Garbutt, DMV. The collection pertains to his his career as a small animal practitioner and his work at the American Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals.</p>  </scopecontent>
